"{\"uid\": \"si.com-college-washington-state-athletics-posts-washington-state-cougars-track-field-2024-olympics-schedule-results\", \"text\": \"Several competitors in the 2024 Paris Olympics can also call themselves Washington State Cougars. Some former and current Cougars are competing in the track and field portion of the games, which officially kicks off on August 1. Follow the Cougars below. All Olympic events are streaming on Peacock and on NBCOlympics.com.  If no results are noted, then they have yet to be determined.  400 Meter Hurdles  Round 1 - August 5, 1:05 AM PT/4:05 AM ET\\u00c2(Results - 48.64, 2nd place in Heat 3, qualified for semi-final))  Repechage Round - August 5, 3:00 AM PT/6:05 AM ET(Did not participate, already qualified for semi-final)  Semi-Final - August 7, 10:35 AM PT/1:35 PM ET(Results - 48.44 seconds, 4th place in Heat 2, did not qualify for final)  Final - August 9, 12:45 PM PT/3:45 PM PT(Did not qualify)  100 Meter Hurdles  Round 1 - August 7, 1:15 AM PT/4:15 AM ET\\u00c2(Results - 13.05 seconds, 8th place in Heat 1, Caicedo moves to repechage round)  Repechage Round - August 8 1:35 AM PT/4:35 AM ET(Results - 12.828 seconds, 2nd place in Heat 2, qualified for semi-final)  Semi-Final - August 9 3:05 AM PT/6:05 AM ET(Results - 12.67 seconds, 4th place in Heat 3, did not qualify for final)  Final - August 10 10:45 AM PT/1:35 PM PT  4x400 Relay  Round 1 - August 9, 1:40 AM PT/4:40 AM ET(Team ran 3:25.77 and qualified for final, but Nijjar did not run)  Final - August 10, 12:22 PM PT/3:22 PM ET  100 Meter Hurdles  Round 1 - August 7, 1:15 AM PT/4:15 AM ET\\u00c2\\u00a0(Results - 12.78 seconds, 4th place in Heat 3, qualified for semi-final)  Repechage Round - August 8 1:35 AM PT/4:35 AM ET(Did not participate, already qualified for semi-final)  Semi-Final - August 9 3:05 AM PT/6:05 AM ET(Results -  12.63 seconds, 3rd in Heat 2. does not qualify for semi-final)  Final - August 10 10:45 AM PT/1:35 PM ET(Did not qualify)  Triple Jump  Qualification - August 2, 11:15 AM PT/2:15 PM ET(Results - Group B 9th Place, Attempt 1: 14.01, Attempt 2: 13.98, Attempt 3: 13.71)  Final - August 3, 11:20 AM PT/2:20 PM ET(Taylor Did Not Qualify)  Note: Former Washington State athlete Louie Hinchliffe, now competing for the University of Houston, will represent Great Britain in the 100m dash, as well as in the 4x100m relay team.  Loading recommendations... Please wait while we load personalized content recommendations  Joe Londergan joined the SI brand in 2023 with G5 Football Daily. With over 15 years of experience in covering and working directly in college and pro sports, Joe's expertise has been featured in Front Office Sports, SB Nation, and XRAY.FM. He is a member of both the Football Writers' Association of America and the National Collegiate Baseball Writers' Association.  Joe holds a bachelor's degree from the University of Louisville and a master's degree in sports administration from Seattle University. Outside of his writing career, Joe enjoys golfing, although he admits that while he hits driver decently, his short game is a liability.  \\u00c2\\u00a9 20262024 ABG-SI LLC-SPORTS ILLUSTRATED IS A REGISTERED TRADEMARK OF ABG-SI LLC. - All Rights Reserved. The content on this site is for entertainment and educational purposes only. Betting and gambling content is intended for individuals 21+ and is based on individual commentators' opinions and not that of Sports Illustrated or its affiliates, licensees and related brands. All picks and predictions are suggestions only and not a guarantee of success or profit. If you or someone you know has a gambling problem, crisis counseling and referral services can be accessed by calling 1-800-GAMBLER.\"}"